article.headline: Fresno State 63, San Jose State 56
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Ja'Vance Coleman scored 15 points and Mustafa Al-Sayyad added 14 points and 10 rebounds as Fresno State defeated San Jose State 63-56 on Sunday in a battle of cold-shooting teams. Marquin Chandler had a game-high 21 points for the Spartans, who shot a season-low 32.3 percent from the field in suffering their sixth straight loss. Dreike Bouldin added 12 points on four three-pointers for the Bulldogs (8-3 overall, 2-0 Western Athletic Conference). San Jose State fell to 3-8 overall (0-2 WAC). Fresno State outrebounded the Spartans 48-31, including a 15-9 edge on the offensive glass. The Bulldogs led by as many 14 points in the second half, 54-40, after Coleman drove for a layup and sank a three-pointer during an 18-second span. Chandler's runner with 3:32 left trimmed the deficit to 56-49, but consecutive inside buckets by Al-Sayyad and Coleman put the game out of reach. Alex Elam added 14 points for San Jose State on 5-of-14 shooting, while Chandler surpassed the 20-point plateau in his fourth straight game. Al-Sayyad scored six of his 14 points in the final 4:42 for Fresno State, which shot 37.9 percent (11-of-29) in both halves. Despite 4-of-18 shooting, Coleman reached double digits in scoring for the 11th consecutive game. The Bulldogs led 33-29 at halftime with both teams shooting below 38 percent from the floor. After grabbing an offensive rebound, Carl Ross found Dwight O'Neil for a three-pointer to give Fresno State its biggest lead of the half, 29-20, with 3:15 left. Chandler had 15 first-half points on 6-of-10 shooting.
